fqnwiiLJ4Xh-r4iV9T1Dlg.text: This place is dangerous!  Cupcakes, cake, brownies, doughnuts, cookies... always an excellent variety of treats, and all very tasty.    Also, Sunday brunch is not to be missed- I've never seen so many vegan breakfast options.  They also allow overflow seating next door at Green, so if the brunch crowd gets hectic, you will still have a nice casual dining experience.

fGHiDOPNh1ZFuUR5SsoLrQ.text: I love ice cream! I have loved ice cream since I was old enough to taste food. When I decided to change my diet to plant based I wasn't sure if I would be able to enjoy ice cream. This place make my dreams come True. I forget it's not made out of dairy. All I know is that it is delicious. Many different varieties for everyone to enjoy copies, pastries, and some simple menu items. I go to Green next door and come here for ice cream afterwards.

5NTT2VduMtBCV6qJoM0JdA.text: VEGAN DONUTS.  Delicious, amazing, glorious VEGAN DONUTS.  WE went for the biscuits and gravy but when we saw these beautiful gems sitting in the case, beckoning us, it was all over.  We had a cinnamon donut.  So fresh, and springy and delightful.  It has been one of the only things I have craved but had been unable to satisfy since transitioning to vegan.  But now, finally, a fabulous solution.    We also enjoyed the biscuits and gravy  and the mcbagel sandwich.  Both were extraordinary.  The B/G was huge.  Next time we will share.  Potatoes were cooked to a beautiful brown perfection.  The Tofu scramble is some of the best I have encountered but the star of the show, by far was the gravy.  Creamy and satisfying with large chunks of "chorizo".  The McBagel sandwich was also a thing of outstanding craftsmanship.  The bagel soft and delicious.  The tofu egg and veggie ham had perfect spice and flavoring.  I'm not sure how they make the "cheese" but it is AMAZING.  This little gem came with a side of fruit.  Boring and expected one may think.  However, this fruit was clearly freshly cut and perfectly ripe.  NO soft grapes, hard cantaloupe or honeydew here my friends.  This was beautiful, bite size chunks of granny smith apple, perfectly ripened strawberries and sweet pineapple.  My one complaint about NAMI.  I live in Mesa and it is in Phoenix.

YeaPm9tmcEe42-80xG5QyA.text: Simply amazing! We grabbed some food here last night before a concert, we live in San Tan Valley, and have zero selections out here for healthier/vegan food..we are about an hour away, everything was perfect, I really wish we had a place that gave a damn about real food and people like me and my family that give a f**k about what goes into our bodies.

J1QnYRvPVUyC40o0GToTmg.text: Those of us who are living the dairy-free lifestyle, whether by choice or allergy, miss ice cream. Any one who says otherwise is lying - especially in the depths of Arizona summer.  So, when your 110-degree world is enlightened by dairy free ice cream that doesn't taste like saw dust and veggie particles, you're likely willing to join a cult just to keep Nami in your life. Though that isn't necessary, yet.  The space downtown is small and parking can be a problem, but it's worth every kind of inconvenience.  But at the end of the day, they put pretzels in soft serve ice cream. So... Five Stars.

hjcZ2GfFraLLajIKb2Z7QQ.text: So, apparently, when I've been here in the past and ordered a macchiato, I was given a CARAMEL macchiato. Which I did not order, but did enjoy. I was under the impression that their macchiato had a bit of caramel drizzled in it. WRONG! Tonight, I ordered a "macchiato, 16oz please" and was informed that it only comes in one size. Previously, more than once, I've ordered a 16 oz macchiato and I explained that to the gal tonight. She asked someone else there, who confirmed they only make it in one size. Ok, fine, I'll have the one size and please make two since I will want more than 12 oz. Then I stood there for 20 minutes, while they made every other customers' tsoynami's, even those who paid after me. I understand, they were busy, but it's just a coffee now.... The gal who rang me up, finally noticed me standing there and apologized, saying they would make my macchiato's right away. Which they did. I get back to work and take the lids off, and they aren't even filled up all the way. What the heck?! Upon sipping, it definitely is NOT the same thing I've received in the past when ordering JUST a macchiato. I never once have ordered it as a caramel macchiato, but I'm realizing now, that must have been what I was charged for, and what was made for me. Moral of my review... get it together guys. I love your products, and you are full of super nice employee's, but there needs to be a bit better communication between each of you, especially when busy, so that a coffee order isn't waiting for 20 minutes. And PLEASE instruct the sweet guy with longer brown hair and glasses, that when a customer orders a macchiato, it only comes in ONE size, and it's not the same thing as a caramel macchiato. ;-)

Nek8WaIDM3Iw6XsAUANXVg.text: I love, love, love Nami!  I am not a vegan but EASILY could be with treats like the ones served there.    The Oatmeal Cream Pie (OCP), chocolate chip cookie, peanut butter and chocolate candy bar, soynamis, etc., etc., etc.  Everything is delicious!    The coffee is also awesome.  In fact, it is so good that I've gone in just for an Americano (and somehow managed to not get a sweet to go with it).    The staff is super-friendly, too.  They are always smiling and pleasant.

Nd4Ym0s7dnUt0mmclzpYEw.text: If you haven't been to Nami stop what you are doing and head over there for some sweet treats!!   Everything is delicious, the craft beer selection goes on for days; I can eat here everyday. Too bad brunch is only from 9-2pm

lCpHnSdA9mvC2mvuZcSuXA.text: one of my favorite places to dine - - - - finally tried breakfast - had biscuits and gravy - - - I've had tufu scramble before, but this one was very dry and tasteless ..grave had great tast, but needed to cover dry biscuits - - - good health should also be tasteful - - - but I still love them

4avjtuuuOGJicXIuuR-6Vg.text: While visiting Phoenix we frequented this place many times. The bakery items were delicious but the biscuits and gravy are a must. The French toast was amazing as well as the breakfast wraps. The tofu scramble was pretty good but the potatoes were generic. The staff was always friendly. The prices are high but I've come to expect that at vegan restaurants.

IMzA9Z6mtpXuqu0JUSEEKg.text: It's close to my work, so anytime I want ice cream, I go here (even though Coldstone is closer). They have awesome flavors. My favorites are the coffee coco loco and there is a special cookie dough one...Awesome. The people that work there are really nice, and if you have a million questions about what kind of cinnamon they use in their cookies, they won't get mad and they'll actually answer. The only downside is the tiny parking lot for Nami+Green, but you can usually make do.

HJKJLY4JSr86H7jnhnbcPg.text: I'm not even a huge "icecream" fan, but holy cannoli! The compost Blizzard-esque concoction was incredible! My husband snarfed the Hostess-esque chocolate cupcake down and said it tasted better than the original! All this goodness without a single animal harmed-yay!

8zsxWnPuenqAr3GwSJzfjQ.text: Great Americanos and lattes. Haven't jumped on their baked good as there is just something off to me about vegan products but I'll leave that stuff to the kids that love it :)  Apparently I need to try their frozen soft-serve thang... Soynami...it's where it's at i keep hearing.   Great great great job on the renovation of the building and thoughtful material choices and design. A very nice addition to 7th street. Nice to see, said the Phoenix native :)

Nya_QBfhuXS2eRcSkLUG3A.text: This place is a great option and concept for some people. Food looks great and is homemade which justifies the prices in this market space until more competitors come into, which I do not see happing soon. Staff is stressed and needs to take a breather and see how they can improve the customer service. That is the only negative with this place so be prepared for it. I hope they can adjust for their demand and improve getting everyone's order out in a timely manner and not just a few, along with a friendly attitude. Good luck to the staff take this as a constructive review. I wish you complete success, support your locals.

OLkwfYZI3hd5SQuFNiAhaQ.text: The cup size is wayyyy smaller now!..it was twice the size a few months ago...they don't fill it to the top all the way either. For $5.50 , i should atleast have it filled up all the way. Sure its delicious..but kinda a letdown. :/ i could get a larger amount for the same price at Loving Hut. The employees have a better attitude. Nami Lost our buisness

bsKlSM25_vCnTHBp9uf5ag.text: Very interesting place. Not at all what I was expecting. I had an iced mocha (geez was it vegan lol? Now I wonder!) which was pretty good. Only drawback was that there was a tiny layer of melted ice at the top which generally indicates the espresso was poured over the ice instead of the proper way of adding the ice last (which may or may not have happened since I wasn't watching it being made, just my observation after years of being a bit of a coffee snob). I also tried the winkie because it was too novel not to. It was... Hard to explain except although it bore no taste resemblance to its toxic namesake, I would definitely eat one again. Very enjoyable and baby loved it too.   I can't give 5 stars simply because I think there are tastier coffee places in town (and whose beans I always buy a crapton of so I can pull shots at home), BUT nevertheless this was a great spot and I'm glad I finally tried it. If you're a diehard vegan this would probably be your favorite coffee place.   Also - on a side note - they charge extra for whipped cream. Kinda weird. As a consumer, nickeling customers for those little extras is off putting. Psychologically, I would rather the prices were a touch higher and included the whipped cream. Just the way the consumer mind works lol.

nCLvK0mkte_0vsU_zO8Olg.text: We went here three times on our vacation. Twice for breakfast and once for their mint tsoynami. My husband loved their pour over coffee. It isn't instant coffee so you need a tiny bit of patience and it's totally worth it. we got breakfast burritos each time and the second time I was feeling like I probably shouldn't do a burrito again and vocalized it and the lady at the counter suggested I do it as a plate-- Not on the menu (that I noticed) and super nice of her. I did and I had no regrets. Their chocolate doughnut was out of this world. Definitely coming back for multiple trips next time I visit family in AZ.

ARlg1pDihbtbC8JcUp_w0Q.text: After school delight with my daughter. Our 1st time here. We loved it! Delicious and a GREAT staff! We will definitely be back!

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. After school delight with my daughter. Our 1st time here. We loved it! Delicious and a GREAT staff! We will definitely be back!

JxRMqj4v2b_AHB7-1PrssQ.text: this place was really hard to find. Once we found it, it was hard to find parking because so many people were there. I got the haystack soynami with chocolate and it was hard to believe that it was vegan. I loved this place and I would come again. The only other complaint, which isnt a real complaint, is that there were so many soynami options that it took me about 10 minutes to decide. Lots of good things, you should come here.

MMsKvMgND2Hxd63uud6qHA.text: Seriously don't go here if you are hungry. I'm pretty patient, but after 20 minutes in line they forgot to make one of our parfaits and then forgot to make one of our entrees. Also a pain in the butt to find parking. The food is pretty good but this is a classic example of how a horrible experience can ruin a good product. Won't be back.

g2L01MVDBy5-KRdQDbbYww.text: Always amazing service and delicious selection of treats to fulfill your Vegan sweet tooth :D BEST Sticky Buns(cinnamon rolls) MUST try but they go quick so get there early! Enjoy

W1syhhTPLJexO1zh1DkPSA.text: Super delicious late night indulgence. We have tsunami banana ice cream and a coconut haystack type of cookie dessert. Both fabulous. When we walked it (we are from out of town) there was no one else there so we were a little worried. We must have hit it just right because it was about 8pm on a Wednesday night. Within 5 minutes of placing our order, the place got super busy. While we ate, it cleared out and filled up again. Everyone seemed to be pretty regular. Nice clean restroom out back - very friendly staff working. If I had any suggestions it would be to have a space planner come in and help figure out better seating. The wall seating was fine but a little awkward because of table placement. People might hang out a little more if the seating was better. We will be back!

NaIxQTi059OePasthQLdvw.text: My best friend and I would get deserts here all the time in Phoenix.  This is hands down one of the best places to go get ice-cream when the hot Phoenix summers are weighing down on you. The staff is friendly and super amazing at helping you find the perfect eats.

rVSjeHJeQ61Osw2l6UFsoA.text: The hazelnut chai drink is top notch! I haven't tried many of the desserts because they are almost always out of everything by the time I get there late at night... but I guess that is a good thing right? They must be good and popular! :P Anyway I'm mainly on here to give a quick shoutout to Arty (spelling?) for being the most happy and friendly worker I have ever encountered in any food place anywhere! :)

vtxiS_8BUgjsbwagIZLoqA.text: I wish there was a Nami in San Diego! This place is sooo DELICIOUS! My husband and I loved their vegan berry cake donuts and Tsoynamis. Can't wait to visit Nami and try more vegan desserts the next time we're in the Phoenix area.

ZJ6D3PsHt3o6uniKWA6_gA.text: Everything is amazing at this place. Favorites are the DONUTS (Raspberry & Maple). Great lattes and a fun atmosphere.   Nice staff and clean place! Would recommend to anyone for breakfast, coffee and ice cream treat.

AL1DasHvo2KoQx6JjPmdeQ.text: Its a bit far from where I live, but I love to come here when I can. Multiple employees are actively participating and leading the animal rights activist movements throughout Arizona, so you know this place is legit.  Thier pastries are excellent, and thier food is similar to greasy fast food... but vegan. I want to emphasize that I mean that last sentence in the best way possible. Where is a vegan supposed to go when he is craving something along the lines of a McGriddle (or whatever they call them these days)? Well we can go to Namis, which is awesome. It satisfys the craving for greasy fast food. I just wish they were open when the bars closed! Either way, I wholeheartedly support what this place represents, and I love thier food and coffee. Also that cookie dough cake that you guys made for my birthday yesterday was awesome. None of my family would have guessed it was vegan (except for the part where I ate it, which kinda gives it way).  Keep up the good work!

qkpSZkBySSh9pObiolj_bA.text: I use to love this place but the last few times the customer service has been the worst. Just tonight, we walked in at least 15 minutes before closing and there was a line if people waiting for ice cream. Randomly, the lady walks out and says "we're not taking any more orders" after we've been waiting for 5 minutes looking at a menu. She was so rude, not even a sorry...I can take my money elsewhere! We walked out and it wasn't even their closing time yet. Rude rude rude and poor customer service all around. Serve the people standing in line, close the door at closing time.

x1Tv0_pjEvP3nokY1rhjmA.text: Vegan blizzards! Their tsyonamis are consistently good and you won't miss the dairy. I especially enjoy the cookie dough one, so much that I haven't tried too many others. The staff is always friendly and they even offered to split our tsyonami so my husband and I could share.

tFxuMzK4NgaeHDUgpMTEVw.text: As good as it gets--great tasting, cruelty-free breakfasts, treats and desserts!  Love the people and the food.  Come, eat, experience joy:-)

r1VnB_A21Btu24CSzNvRzQ.text: I've been going to Phoenix's Nami for years. What used to be one of my favorite vegan establishments has become a place that causes me to leave regretting wasting my money. The food and beverages continue to be great, but accompanied by awful service! Tonight I ordered a simple iced espresso drink before I go into work. I watched the two customers ahead of me get their orders and leave. Then I sat for 8 minutes while the five employees did anything but make my drink. I was the ONLY customer in the restaurant at this point, and clearly sitting there waiting for my order. It took another customer coming in and getting their coffee immediately after ordering to finally say, "Hey, is my drink going to be made?" They all looked at each other and started making it (took 30 seconds to make - not 9 minutes like I waited) but not a single apology from any of them, let alone eye contact. A guy made the drink, set it on the counter and walked away quickly. So glad I spent $6 on a beverage and was treated with such awful customer service! As someone in the restaurant industry, I know mistakes happen but this kind of treatment to a paying customer is never acceptable!

_5aPeySoQqclD90l9dV2ew.text: The serving size for the "tsoynami" (soy soft serve blended with treats) was pretty generous!  Not Costco yogurt generous but still a nice large size for $4.50 before tax and tip.  I chose the mint Newman O one (don't recall the cutesy menu name).  It was really a lot better than I excepted.  It could've used another pump or two of mint syrup/flavor though, and the chocolate syrup tasted a little cheap (like Hershey's).  Pulling into the parking lot was not fun, but thankfully they weren't crowded and it wasn't rush hour yet!  Overall, a nice non-dairy alternative to the Blizzards and Concrete Mixers of the world.

iJLk1eVjuA5_PxYZcIUbjA.text: This is the most overwhelming and beautiful place in the valley..it is definitely not for the indecisive. I am used to having a few vegan options at the average froyo shop or bakery, but here it is like vegan jesus created every amazing dessert in 7 days.   The Mash is definitely the best and a gamble..so even better, especially because you can tell that the employees love making it and telling customers about it. I have never regretted ordering it. The only thing that you should worry about is spending too much because..it WILL happen.  ps bring some cash to tip with/ vote for your favorite theme of the day. its fun and the employees deserve a tip. when I was there it was zombies versus vampires and..being the walking dead fan that I am, it made it the easiest decision I had while I was there.

aVcKJXD7lzjKfXV4Eaku5Q.text: Recently I found out I'm allergic to eggs.  I thought my sweets-loving life was over... That is until my friend brought me to Nami just around the corner from my home. They have so many baked goods that are completely vegan - that means no eggs!  They are good too.  I've attempted to make eggless goodies and most of them do not come out well.  Nami has many selections such as snickerdoodles and chocolate chip cookies.  Most recently, I had a tsoynami with cookie dough and other chocolately goodness in it.  It was one of the best desserts ever!   I'm happy to know I can cruise over on my bike the next time I have a sweet tooth rather than having to make something myself.

4DlU-uQIX0i2WTTEQpmbMA.text: Tsoynamis are one of my favorite foods in the world. I'm lactose intolerant and love blizzards, so it's a match made in heaven. I go to Green a lot as I live nearby, and have never felt unwelcome there, so I had no reason to think I'd feel that way about their sister joint, Nami. So after a disappointing dinner at Nobou at Teeter House in downtown phx, bf and I were excited to turn our night around with dessert at Nami when we realized we were super close to it and it was still open (since Green would have been closed by the time we got there). Their hours posted indicate they close at 9:30pm on Fridays, and we arrived at 9:20 after calling to confirm they were still open.   We walked in, and there were a few groups of people sitting and leisurely enjoying their ice cream and baked goods. We walked up to the counter and bf knew what he wanted right away (s'mores tsoynami with pb added...SO good!). I, on the other hand, needed a minute to decide since they had a huge bakery case filled with things I never see at Green and wanted to try out, in addition to the full tsoynami menu.   I asked a few questions, which the light-haired woman working there was happy to answer. She disappeared to make bf's tsoynami, though, and we were then met with an icy stare and complete annoyance by the dark-haired woman working there. I like to give people the benefit of the doubt, and hey, it's Friday night and she probably wanted to close up so she could go out. But it wasn't even 9:30, and she had zero interest in making this customer happy.   I said I was debating between a cookie and a tsoynami, while she rolled her eyes and continued to tap her fingers on the counter. Her response, rather than a suggestion or recommendation for something to order, was, "We close in five minutes." Ok? I know that already? Why wouldn't you just try to hurry us along in a constructive way, rather than making me feel afraid to ask you any questions about your products?  She continued to sigh and look around, willing us to disappear, and honestly I wish we would have left right then. But we were starving, and I really wanted to enjoy one of their delicious looking treats. I decided in my head that I wanted a tsoynami, but I was way too afraid to have that lady actually prepare something for me as I was pretty sure she would spit in it, in addition to the length of time it would have taken to prepare which surely would have put us over her 5-minute limit. I said I'd take the cookie, to get us out of there sooner. We still had to wait another minute for bf's tsoynami to be finished, and felt her stare us down the whole time. Mind you, there are still parties of other customers at tables still lingering. We were definitely NOT responsible for keeping them open, but we sure were made to feel that way!  I don't care how tasty your treats are, I would never EVER go back there...who wants to leave a dessert place with such a sour taste in their mouth? I will be getting all of my future tsoynamis at Green, where they never make me feel like I'm doing something wrong by asking questions or spending a minute debating between a few items.

XPhB8bRnu50iRvhlKnkVuA.text: This is such a great Vegan coffee and dessert spot, even though I am not a Vegan or Vegetarian I love the yumminess they have here and once you have a Nami you will fall in love with their soy goodness!!! My favorite is Dez Hazelnuts however they don't have that one here at this new location only the one in Tempe.  All coffee drinks come with soy at no additional charge, however if you want hazelnut, almond or pecan there is an additional charge not more than .50 cents. and right across the way there is Green the vegetarian restaurant. With this new set up only food is served at Green and only desserts at Nami.  I like this location as it is not too far from route 51 on my way to and from work so I can stop and get a Fair Trade latte that rivals Starbucks.

Oz_k3is7JDvf_ADo5_4bCA.text: Very tasty vegan ice cream... tasted incredibly creamy, with a vanilla and coconut base. I loved it. I got the thin mint ice cream and I relished in every bite.  They also use wooden spoons, which are a weird dry texture on  your mouth, but still pretty neat.  Would definitely go back.

gPweA03F_1ZimbaLmU7kjw.text: Was pleasantly surprised with the PB&J tSoynami. Never had tried Vegan soft serve... I would get this again though

vnDa0BiIx2jOuUgF7HMQjQ.text: Went in there today for the hundredth time. I ordered a cupcake that is the vegan equivalent of a chocolate hostess cupcake. Amazing! They also have great coffee drinks, other pastries and vegan blizzards. Yum! On the occasional Sunday I will take friends to their brunch.

ExlZsXse6h3U5hp3L2uhHA.text: The best place for dietary restrictive date nights! If you don't have any dairy issues, you'll still love this place. Sooo good!   Good things take time, so be prepared for your yummy to take a bit of time. It's made when you order.

l-OJm9y0k4ZbeqPfUqLGkw.text: This place has the best vegan treats I have tried. The ice cream is delicious, not too sweet but not too bland. The cookies taste almost like regular dairy cookies, same with the cheesecake. The staff is very friendly and helpful. Prices are fair. If you're ever in the area and craving something sweet you should give this place a try!

QJYujUyMjlF_nxACIWILxw.text: I was so excited when Nami opened. It's a great compliment to the already amazing Green. Nami has pretty much everything you'd want in terms of sweet as a vegan.   Great pastries,coffee,doughnuts, and ice cream treats as well as a rotating Sunday brunch. I've never had a bad thing at this place and that's no exaggeration.  It can get pretty crowded in there during peak hours but honestly the service is fast enough that I never worry.  Check this place out for sure.

1VueSeGxrZVGNXX6KKJU4w.text: This place is so cute! We came here for breakfast and everything was delicious, the big ole breakfast burrito is probably the best burrito I've ever had. We got ice cream and pastries to go too :)

ezUPgkV471M355jLdc7ndA.text: I like this place. My favorite is the oatmeal creme cookie when I can have it on rare occasions. Coffee is ok, but I see most people eating ice cream when I come for a visit. That said, please clean up the place between customers. Tables are always nasty and not wiped down after each customer. I have been in Nami dozens of times, but have never seen anyone cleaning tables.

2a-6oMc0pKe6H14Vq4JXRQ.text: OMG, Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough tSoynami is like crack to me! My favorite ice cream before going vegan was Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough so I was psyched when I saw this here. I was not disappointed! No, it's not as creamy as "real" ice cream, but it beyond hit the spot for me. LOVE, LOVE, LOVE IT!   I did order some other desserts. I'm sure they were okay, but nothing could hold a candle to that cookie dough. I think it put me in a heavenly dessert blackout. I believe we also ordered Lavender Tea cookies, White Chocolate Raspberry cupcake, and Vanilla and Chocolate milkshakes. Don't judge!   As everyone has mentioned, the parking is a nightmare. I went at an off time to minimize the trauma as I drive a CUV. My passenger had to get out and guide me into a space. It was sooo worth it. I would do it again!

ujXPqr0MjrqmfpIe4sgDbA.text: Great little place! Nice to see something different like this in Arizona. The sister restaurant next door is excellent.  Had a soy-ft serve sundae, awesome. Had an iced coffee, so delighted by all the options for vegan-friendly milk (soy, almond, rice, etc).   Great place, good luck!  1 thing - the wood spoons, while I'm sure are biodegradable and all, have a weird texture with the ice cream (at least for me). I think those spoons just kind of freak me out. I didn't ask for plastic or metal, I'm sure they would have accommodated.

j3w4DOOBRRhXDw0PEAPGVQ.text: Vegan breakfast  includes donuts, acai bowls and some salads. The food was not the best tasting or texture. My friend got an acai bowl that was huge and soupy. The donut was okay, the salad was a little rich for a breakfast item and a big portion. Not my favorite place.

IDmXX4vNaRq6jlu6rEmRJQ.text: I've been meaning to check out nami for a while now so we finally popped in this past Sunday as we are doing a vegan challenge. They have really yummy vegan desserts! If you are thinking of using the wifi though its pretty spotty but otherwise a great place to chill! On Sunday evenings they have live music as well which is nice.

YQTmHUpT0rzw5INbtpJN0g.text: Nami is really a one-of-a-kind place. I love what they're doing and what they stand for; good vegan restaurants in Phoenix are few and far between. It's rad that they offer a few raw options now- the raw power breakfast is soso good. I will say that some of the staff at Nami is extremely unfriendly and sometimes rude, acting as if the customers are an inconvenience to them. However, Katie is always really nice. Overall, I'm a fan and will continue to come back but their coffee isn't very strong and that makes me sad.

Mp5XAl17G6K_LDCI9-1fKw.text: I have myself believing that a tsoynami is not bad for me. Please do not feel obligated to comment otherwise. Anybody. Thanks.

z3E0L93Kt90aoq8EPuhRQA.text: I'm a vegetarian and have a laundry list of food allergies, yet there is always something at Nami that I can eat, and not only that, but I can actually enjoy it. The cupcakes are great and so are the different tsoynamis. I like to get the ones with cereal in them, but that's me. Most of my friends are not vegan/veg at all and still really enjoy this place, there really is something for everyone, and I've always had very friendly people working there help me when I don't know what I want. Nami is great!

iXkhzIEMq3Vwyuiq69NJ1g.text: I came here looking to try some new vegan options in my life. Thinking at the very least it would help my hangover. What i found was more than i could have imagined.  A unique venue with two buildings one housing a cafe-esque ordering are and the other the kitchen with enclosed dinning that allows just enough of the outside in to be pleasant. The staff was courteous and attentive. The options numerous and bounding with eccentric platters.   Moving along, the important thing here is FOOD people , and it was amazing. While most things seem to mimic meat dishes with chorizo and eggs on the menu, Nami pulls of these imitations by making insanely more delicious vegan plates.  I was blown away by my "Chicken wings" the sauce was unlike anything i have had before and i was instantly in love. My OJ based concoction was also amazing as it had some kind of red syrup in the bottom that complimented the not too sweet OJ.   Street pedestrians are not disruptive to your dinning experience and provides ample opportunity to people watch.   All in all this place is a must go location if your trying for a healthy, creative, and delicious meal in Phoenix.

c0i5F_wH2thoZndvv6RPEw.text: Had the cookie dough ice cream and espresso shake (it's not on the menu, but you can request it). Both were good. The cookie dough chunks were HUGE, and the espresso shake was what you expect it to taste like. The portion size for the ice cream is pretty big. One order is share-able in my opinion.

FgqNApxXNfLUq43XXHlPeg.text: This place is full of health conscious treats. I got one of the soynamis and it was SO good. I typically do not like soft serve but this is different. My stomach doesn't hurt at all and I don't feel heavy afterwards.  So many different options in terms of flavors and options too. I think they should definitely make more locations!  I just wish there was better parking.. but all in all great place with great sweets!

XqmaCeDXGhpvmRwwJWb1OA.text: First non-dairy ice cream I've LOVED! I got the doughboy which tastes just like dairy cookie dough ice cream. Woo! A little pricey at $5+ BUT definitely split with a friend - more than enough ice cream. Thanks Nami. Will be back.

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Doughboy vanilla

Ie_Nho3SnCwaiKSkzVlZPw.text: Lot's of great things to try! The burgers and fries are my favorite so its hard to choose. I just need to make frequent visits!

HegUJq86xWr03akw-nNgNw.text: Surprised this soft-serve is 100% vegan!! You can't even tell the difference, and it's indulgent without being overwhelming sweet or heavy. I've tried a majority of the items on the menu (I'm an ice cream fiend) and I have enjoyed all of them. They have friendly employees and a nice space for catching up with your buddies. I've never tried their coffees or baked goodies because I go there for the soft serve, but I'm sure those are good too.   Lately, I've been trying out the "Mystery Mash Up" which is a soft serve masterpiece that is up to the discretion of the employee of the hour. Examples of what has been in my mash-up include red velvet cupcake, Concha Mexican bread, carrot cake. (All of which were vegan too!) If you're feeling gutsy when you stop by, the mash up is for you!   BUT, my all-time favorite combo is the Doughboy with Vanilla soft serve and replace the chocolate syrup for pretzels!! It's the best mix of sweet, salty, crunchy, and creamy. Try it and let me know what you think!

1iTJVZIaKA7wzHD6wwVtCQ.text: If I could give 10 stars I would. This place is like heaven. I love eating Vegan sweets.

If6FP9fJhEaaNyTPMjBUXA.text: Update! I've been back to Nami twice recently for brunch and you simply must stop in here on a Sunday to have this tasty food!  If you see on their social media that they're running the "Flying Saucer" brunch special, reschedule your weekend and be sure to go get this.  It is a large deep fried tortilla bottom, topped with all of the goodness... daiya cheddar, enchilada sauce, soyrizo, hominy, black beans, tofu scramble, fried potatoes, lettuce, pico, guac, sour cream and more red sauce on the side.  You probably won't eat the whole thing, but its kind of fun to try!  The line for brunch is at Nami, which is where you'll place your order and get a number to take to your table.  Green is not open for their menu, but you can sit inside the restaurant and order drinks there, and of course the patio is open. Sangria is in a HUGE mason jar, they have bloody marys and local beers.  There are donuts, and I can confirm the apple fritter is a solid 7.5 out of 10.  Good coffee too if you need a pick me up!

MFYRUvpKkdpkbcdM-XKFfQ.text: I wish I could give this more than 5 stars! I had been seeing this place all over social media and finally got around to trying it-- I had definitely been missing out! Amazing vegan ice cream that doesn't have the gross aftertaste- plus it's soft serve! This is the only place I know of that has this and it's cheap too!   This is probably going to become a bad habit for me because it was so good. Loved it!

ZdbUIxOf_mhRF5KRmuOegA.text: The first time I came to visit my (vegan) daughter in July-2018, she couldn't wait to bring me to her favorite hot spot. I LOVED it! Since then it's become a must-visit. My omnivore son-in-law loves it too! You scream, I scream, we all scream for NAMI vegan ice-cream!!!

7_Pkbl47Nevs7qQQX8h3QQ.text: 4.5!This is a small place, kind of hard to find parking but it's definitely worth it! They serve breakfast there as well but I mainly came for desserts.  Everything there is vegan! I love their vegan soft serve! There should definitely have more locations though!  First, you chose chocolate, vanilla or swirl for a base then chose the toppings they have on the menu. Kind of like a vegan blizzard! It's really good! You can't really tell the difference tbh.   I got their doughboy with chocolate ice cream, coffee coco with swirls, cookies and cream with vanilla ice cream, and fruity soynamins! I absolutely love them all but their doughboy is the best! Taste exactly like normal cookie dough. Definitely should try!

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Chai tiramisu with added cookie dough  / chocolate ice cream base
Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States
Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Cookies and cream w/ vanilla base

MJSaY-4bT_NPrCyn6FvVIw.text: Love this place. While in Phoenix I came here almost every morning.  What's not to like about this place? Food, service, desert all great. I wish this was a big chain with location  in many other cities.

tI9g8tAwtMRuzf_aODCw6A.text: This is place is probably the greatest restaurant I have ever been to. Vegan cookies, vegan donuts, vegan ice cream and sundaes?? What's not to love? The staff were very kind, as well, and the place itself was clean and cool. We all ordered a different sundae and they were so delicious. I also love that they are right next to Green New American. Can't wait to come back for donuts.   Pictured below is the S'mores soynami. GET IT.

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States

jb23V3OOHnipG0-twtZ8Wg.text: I love love love this place. It's so nice to get vegan drinks, cookies, ice cream, cupcakes, etc. that are actually delicious. They're is a huge shortage of vegan restaurants in AZ, so finding this and Green were a pleasant surprise. I have yet to try their breakfast but I have high hopes.

F9psS0XGyqgFUzTFlVuxZg.text: Fabulous Vegan treats from folks that obviously care. My only tiny complaint might be that the pricing is on the high side of what I'm willing to pay for vegan treats, when I'm not actually a vegan. I go here because it's one of the few places in Phoenix that offers a vegan dessert menu that is actually very good. But, as a non-vegan, I've had all of their offerings, made by non-vegan ingredients in other restaurants, or even in my own kitchen, and while Nami is good, it's not as good, as the original. But don't get me wrong, Nami does a outstanding job of creating vegan versions of many treats.

QqcSh191dqSLnSSVjv6gGw.text: As a vegan it can be super hard to find good places to satisfy my sweet tooth. This place does just that. The desserts are delicious and are also very generously portioned. Will definitely be coming back

Zt7n9HxUdERhjUrgVwi_og.text: The vegan ice cream is very good, you definitely wouldn't guess it was vegan. The flavors are good and there's lots of options. Costs 5-5.50 but it's equivalent to 2-3 scoops of ice cream. Pretty good price for what you get.

oM944tLZb4HA8GZ3RHj_Nw.text: So amazing, I went back for seconds the next day! Great place to stop in while you wait for your food at the neighboring Green New American Vegetarian restaurant.

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Vanilla Affogatto
Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. &#34;Betterfinger&#34; Vanilla tSoynami
Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Vegan treats

OYZNC6bE-ZlQ6srjuI3Xiw.text: Sweet creamy satiating cool down with Vegan vanilla with chunks of chocolate drops and pecans!

yLY8EiuGF3ArUZr2BMJzJQ.text: Vegan baked goods yes!!! I had the cactus haboob latte with cinnamon agave and it was so deliciously refreshing. Not too sweet and substituted with almond milk, it was even more bomb!! The peach cobbler swirl was very good too. Vegan nami chocolate chip cookie was so good minus the guilt because of vegan ingredients.  This spot was right next to the vegan restaurant that had the best stuff in their menu as well. You must visit both while parked in the Lot!! Friendly staff and both great ambiance for small groups. Not recommended for big parties as seatings are limited. Would recommend highly.

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Inside
Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Cactus haboob latte with almond milk
Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Peach cobbler swirl

9PKAfX0BTGEiuCOf6kBmvQ.text: Probably one of the best vegan tacos I've ever had! The mushrooms were so tasty without being overly sauteed or greasy. Our service was great, we walked into their margarita happy hour (coincidentally)  and the aesthetic of the place is very cute! What more could you want from a good taco spot?

o62iNc_qIQBuNgzlkAFHig.text: If you ever need to satisfy that sweet tooth, but most restaurant dessert menus are plagued with items you can't eat, come HERE! I've had their caramel mockiato which is great! For someone who is lactose intolerant, their vegan pastries are a godsend! Their carrot cake cupcake was so good, a little too sweet for my preference, but so so decadent. Late night dessert with a friend visiting AZ called for some Tsoynamis and their almond oy vey was perfect!

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Caramel mockiato and a carrot cake cupcake

xcQxUpRkZxE9fNkB72C2kg.text: Although I usually do like vegan/soy-based ice cream, I didn't like the actual ice cream here too much. I got a tsoynami, and the mix-ins helped make it a little more enjoyable. It's really just a matter of taste, so I would definitely try it for yourself before writing it off. My boyfriend actually loved his tsoynami, and I definitely want to try some of their donuts and pastries so I certainly will stop in this place again.   The location is good, it's pretty easily accessible, and there is plenty of parking. The staff is friendly enough, and it was very clean inside and out.

l6TGEfWEHlYpoKjCvQy9zA.text: I'm not vegan but I gave up all meat and dairy for the first week of lent. Decided to come here with a friend because I was craving ice cream. Staff is very nice and friendly, location is perfect and plenty of parking. I got the banana cream pie and it was actually good. I could tell it wasn't regular ice cream because I know and love my dairy, so the imitation  whip cream was what gave it away -and honestly didn't care for and next time I will ask to have it without it - but the rest was fine. The sweetness was on par and was not too overly done, as a lot of healthy food places try to do to cover up the bad taste, the add tons of sugar. The crinkles in my ice cream gave a crunch and a nice added flavor. I'd definitely come back and would love to try other flavors. It was a good experience and I am hoping I can find my new vegan ice cream flavor.

BMzCrBRdLD_a3C7wfgomPA.text: I'll drive across town just for a soynami  Don't forget to grab one of their gluten free cheesecakes while you're there too! Great service and the best deserts!

CFXtOZaf8_QKHolPHYo1Pw.text: A cute small place with delicious treats! So worth the late night snack :p   It's one of the unique places in phx

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. One of the views
Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Something captain

Lpd9HIAdxAmcoWb16EYkfA.text: My family and I love this place! My daughter was just diagnosed with like 20 food allergies and this place was one of the only allergy friendly options I had to take her so she knew that there were still good food options out there. So important for a teenager to know!! And the food is yummy too!!

LUTS3F0nCnHIK90F1uXQqw.text: I love this vegan dessert place. The banana cream tsoynami was great. But I think the whipped cream is made with coconut milk, which I hate. There wasn't too much of it and the ice cream itself had a really nice texture, so I ignored the whipped cream.  The chai tsoynami had excellent flavors and some type of crunchy graham crackers mixed inside. So yummy! The white chocolate raspberry donut, which was also gluten free, was not so good. The flavor was kinda funky and we couldn't finish it.  I would love to return to try other things next time I'm in AZ.

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Banana cream tsoynami and a vegan donut in the box

SEMbZnFQhdJzCKRnb4hFwg.text: Going to nami, I wasn't really sure what to expect. I recently made a lifestyle change of wanting to eat more of a plant based diet for my health so hearing about a vegan dessert place was pretty cool. However, I was not impressed with my experience. It seems as if they try to make up for lack of flavor by dumping pounds of sugar into their desserts. Seriously some of the sweetest things I've ever eaten. Texture of ice cream was okay but the aftertaste was not pleasant. I did like the snickerdoodle cookie but overall I do not see myself returning due to the lack of True flavor and crazy amounts of sugar in their desserts.

J-tGQ2AXst3vM5XfZz2TJw.text: The vegan Samoa bar was HUGE--enough for two people. Totally something to share! Nice ambience, too.

O2D3W2FlsniJjvEc3LmObw.text: This place is my saving grace. I can't eat dairy or gluten and this has an option for both! everything they have is vegan. Some things are gluten free. It's amazing. The staff is also super friendly.  Parking is a bit weird, but not too terrible for a downtown area. I'll always come back to this place!

SnOKaJ-R5yry3YQO-xff-w.text: This place is pretty great for vegan treats. Nestled near the heart of downtown phoenix, the atmosphere is pretty nice even though the parking situation is always an adventure. I always try different flavors of the "ice cream" and am pleasantly surprised each and every time. Oh so good! Super friendly and attentive staff as well! Can't beat that combination.

fbaCVGH8pCqbTcqsJLPLJg.text: Love this place!!!  When I get downtown I try to eat here.  There is nothing really bad about Nami or Green except parking.   I have never ate anything I disliked there.  They are accommodating to groups of people too.   I hope they expand to the west side or north side of Phoenix!

zHV7wiJ8jt5AmTPV_h1dmA.text: Oh my gosh, I take everyone here! I love this place so much. Unfortunately I have a lactose intolerance, so ice cream is a no-no, but this place makes vegan ice creammmm YAY!! I've tried everything on the menu and it's all so delicious:) they also have a bunch of vegan pastries if you are into that!

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. They are so delicious :P

I8DMIbB01dsX-y3TgbiFdA.text: Excellent gluten free doughnuts.  Almost as good as revolution doughnuts in Atlanta.  And that is high praise!!

4aDXLYy9wLFtIGRrb1N-nA.text: A+!!! Love this place! Yummy delicious food and amazing service! Being a vegan has never been better!

XZq4hlrfVwzxlAiQbeQmng.text: Sadly disappointed. I ordered multiple items to try some of their stuff out. And the only thing I was content with was the Italian soda i ordered. The other items were either too strong in a flavor or not strong enough. The ice cream was alright as well. Just wasn't all that for me i guess. And I've had plenty delicious vegan treats to know that vegan treats can be way better then dairy treats. And these did not make that list.

id7Gc_MD3BBob1EmJmeCSw.text: We went there today to try it out what the hype was all about. Sorry this place is overrated. They make those vegan "ice cream shakes" with no love into them whatsoever. They look like someone ate it and it came out of them again. Your eyes eat with!!!  I had to search for my mango and berries that were supposed to be in them. Vegan gluten free donut also not tasty. It tasted like a cheap packed ready mix. To pricey for what it is. I love trying new things especially little places, but nope there is better places in and around PHX then this.  2 Stars only because they are somehow trying to make a "healthy" version of a cafe vs a chain.

8m4u-8FJI_JtuD5Rx7jMoA.text: This is an excellent place to go after enjoying a Big Wac (aka best vegan burger in the world...believe me, I travel a ton for work and have tried many) next door at Green Vegetarian (literally next door, same parking lot). I've tried all kinds of things from Nami and everything has always great (e.g., vegan twinkies, donuts, etc.). The item of praise this go around has to be the soft serve ice cream, for which there was a 25 minute wait--that's how popular it is!  If you're in town a few days, Green Vegetarian and Nami are a must.

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Vegan snacks.
Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Vegan soft serve.

15cqKByaDbLeg1qAMeejHQ.text: Sunday brunch was fantastic! 100% plant based but never felt deprived at the selection. We started with Sin-a-bun and a vegan GF donut.  (We weren't here to lose weight). Shared 2 plates chilaquiles, vegan huevos rancheros, and side of  southwestern grits.  All were quite good and generous portions. Potatoes were perfect.  Eclectic vibe and solid coffee quality.  Wish I had room to try the biscuits and gravy- maybe next time. Great wait staff and counter service.  Some items were expensive but quality is worth it.  If this is the trend of food, we're going that direction gladly.

knjV_r4PpmQqR4hCATwzZw.text: This place is soooo cute. I've never had dairy-free ice cream before and I was surprised by how good it was! It was sooooo delicious, the chocolate flavor was especially tasty! I look forward to going back!

2kTWrGdz1AYmUknXUEsapQ.text: Nami is our favorite Phoenix vegan bakery/brunch spot. The coffee is always really good - I consistently order a hot almond milk latte and my bf gets the cold brew. The cold brew is minimally tangy/acid and has a smooth caramel undertone. Donuts are always good, but the weekend selection is much better than mid week. Sunday Brunch has a different menu from the rest of the week, and it is amazing! Most recently we visited on a weekday and I ordered a delicious breakfast kale salad with homemade seed crisps with a cashew sauce in the side. So much flavor. My bf got the Wing Ding Dang burrito filled with 'wings', avocado, tempeh, and other crazy good fillings. We're lifetime subscribers to this place :)

we2zYo9XZ-5aiqYfSscLpg.text: The tSoynamis are wonderful. They are expensive, but is a nice once-in-a-while treat.  My only suggestion to the manager: Please place PRICES on your pastries and sweets displayed in the glass case. (ie. doughnuts, muffins, cake, etc). I'm not in favor of unpriced items.  It is a slight inconvenience for me to have to ask your staff member what the prices are on each item-I don't want to hold up the line. I want to do the math and make my selections BEFORE approaching the register. I think others would feel the same way.  Pricing each item (sweets in the window) gives courtesy to your customers and holds the business accountable for accuracy in numbers. This ensures that the customer knows exactly how much he/she is being charged for tax.

v1O5_E5YYZ3cwbru0F6NQg.text: The fact that I have yet to write my review of Nami should be an insult to vegans and sweet lovers everywhere!  Nami, short for Tsoynami, is heaven on earth. or the moon. jupiter. wherever there is heaven, there is Nami.  Soy "tsoft" serve ice cream. Winkies. Snickerdoodles. Various cupcakes. Various cakes. Coffee with a choice of soy, almond, rice, and even hazelnut milk!  Although they have only done it once, Nami is planning on running a regular Sunday brunch in February. I thought it was amazing when I went to the beta test. Multiple scramble options in addition to chilaquilles and other brunch creations.   Do yourself a favor and stop by. If not for the treats, for the awesome dancing and singing always taking place!  PS... Cheddar and Chive Scone (thank me anytime)

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Nami!!

xqXs6Df7gEiaH0x8_5RNwg.text: best vegan donuts in AZ! and the nami mc muffin sandwich is equally amazing. love this place, the food is always exceptional and the staff is really nice as well. i would recommend, and say its a must if you live here  or are traveling through phoenix.

MJTwCpMXvpeAF7w_MrV40g.text: I was in Phoenix for just 2 days and managed to hit this spot up twice!!!! I really wish they had one in LA.  All vegan blizzards, tons of baked goods=my paradise!  My favorites were the Monsoon special (choc cake, choc chips, and choc syrup) which I added PB too and another one with pretzels, PB and chocolate chips.  Can't wait to come back on my next trip to Phoenix. They have a sister veg restaurant next door that I can't wait to try too (yes I may have just eaten Tsoynamis for dinner).

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. &#34;Monsoon&#34; special (choc cake, choc chips, choc syrup) w/ added PB

13eHF2EiWy-h7wXeDe4s_Q.text: Such delicious ice cream! Perfect spot for amazing food with dietary needs like gluten free and dairy free.

q7Gu4n5trK8WcvHFahwBCQ.text: This is my first time here and my gf ordered the macadamia nut milk latte and the strawberry fritters. We loved it all. Even thinking about going back to grab more of the fritters and trying out their breakfast. It's hard to find a good vegan joint around phoenix. The search is over! Definitely will be coming back to try other stuff on the menu.

Ntfkr3wCl3u_kqztYxX7cA.text: Nami is the place to go when you are looking for a yummy treat (vegan or not)! The doughboy tsoynami is my favorite and a close second is the NO's n Mint. You cant go wrong with any tsoynami flavor honestly. I would pretty much recommend everything, other than the peanut butter bar thing they sell at the front and the baked chocolate chip cookies, which I have found to be a little hard and dry. The staff are always super friendly and helpful, and the whole place is super chill. Sometimes its a little busy, but the line usually moves  quickly, and the wait time to get your yummy treat is not long at all. I have taken my non vegan friends here and everyone loves it too! Honestly I cant get enough!!

zkbGZuDhH0zYZ16pnBAURQ.text: VEGAN SOFT SERVE!!!  I was recently in Phoenix for a concert, and had a day to kill, so I searched around for good vegan spots in Phoenix.  Nami did not disappoint!  I had a Tsoynami, and a cupcake.  Man, the cupcakes look small, but they're sooooo rich!  Filling and delicious!  I couldn't even finish it all in one sitting!  The soft serve is so good and so unique to this location I keep finding myself searching for excuses to visit Phoenix.  I'll be back, for more Tsoynami!

RVpXQNEKztH4pyaHv8OfBw.text: So I come here any chance I get and figure it's about time I give back some love.  This place is amazing.  I usually come for the tsoynamis, which are never disappointing. Better than real, dairy-based ice cream!! They have great treats and baked goods, smooth espresso, and friendly staff. Never have I had a bad experience here.    You won't regret it! Promise!

lcppxDlDRKMAofyG9MbHDg.text: If you're going to close at 2pm instead of 9:30pm the least you could do is update Yelp so that we don't drive 30 minutes to find a closed shop!!! Was hoping to pick up some treats before my flight and now I'm left with nothing.

5Jes0PV9mwIXMKLT2ewx7Q.text: Saw a friend posts photo about this place and decided to give the place a try. The server was very helpful and knowledgable of the menu items. We made it too late for brunch so we ended up trying some of their tsoynamis (cookie dough and cookies and cream). They were delicious considering it was a vegan dessert. Didn't even notice that there was no diary. Also had their cosmic cookie and it was delicious especially mixing it with the tsoynamis!

pNGDciWjJyWcrmPVcflsCA.text: Here is the deal with Nami. I like you, I do but you just aren't friendly.  I have been in there multiple times and I would love to buy multiple things but I feel like I am bothering all of you.   Tonight I asked a question about ice cream.  I wanted enough to take home for me and my roommate to share AND have some for the weekend.  But you never let me get there and I ended up with a cup full of ice cream for just him.  My advice would be take the time to find out what someone wants completely before checking out of the conversation.  And don't look complete pissed when I ask you what something is. It makes me feel like I am bothering you and it makes you look like a jerk.  I will say if there was another place to go that had everything you did I would never go to you again until you changed your wicked ways.

RDzdIOsGQzAlqQmq3Yr7ag.text: What can I say,  other than absolutely delicious and  amazing. Everyone is always nice, love the ambience,  and is truly a gem. Definitely take everyone there,  even if you think you don't like non dairy treats- you will discover that you do.

qmQxRYPlgwnmpn69GH34kQ.text: We love Nami.  After eating at Green, we always go to Nami to see what they have.  Their menu is always changing for many of their baked items.  I wish they had some carob desserts.

gv6MpyHPb3NczmxTCs4yyQ.text: Cool little spot.  Service was average, nothing spectacular.  We tried the Nami stuff. Different, but good.

u9I7sLx3MbKKugQMb78m8A.text: OK, each star represents a visit during my less-than-48 hour visit to PHX. YES, I WENT TO NAMI FIVE TIMES IN TWO DAYS. Don't judge. Vegan soft serve is hard to find, people.  3 trips were for tSoynamis.  AMAZING!!!!!!!!!!  had Fluffernutterin, Chai Tiramisu & S'mores.  brought non-vegan friends & they loved it, too.  2 trips were for coffee. the lattes were yummy.  also had a yogurt parfait, delish!  Amazing looking pastries- saving that for next time.  Staff are super friendly & hip & helpful.

F3hjvvEK7PBmmejynuL2jw.text: Excellent alternative to froyo and the normal packed coffee house in the neighborhood. Nice atmosphere. Easy place to work on papers or meet with friends. Good coffee, good sweets, and good frozen treats. Try a tsoynami with some frozen fruit and be open to trying some vegan quiches. Parking is scarce, so be sure to carpool. Get your hipster fix in an unpretentious way.

photos.caption: Photo of Nami - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Drink of the Week: What the Flax, Iced Cactus Haboob &amp; a Baked (!) Cardamom Spiced Donut

U160RmQj9AlXHqPTQg-B_A.text: It's really difficult to add anything original here because everyone else has already said it, but this place is simply amazing!  I have never tried anything here that I didn't like.  Their lattes especially are delicious.  The iced chai tastes very similar to Starbucks, for anyone who has become vegan and is no longer able to drink Starbucks chai because it has honey in it.  I also recommend the raspberry mocha.  All of their cupcakes and the McBagel and the burritos are great, too.  Just try the whole menu.  You won't regret it.

DU3AlHsvFbrzkW6T9J-tag.text: A great place for vegan desserts and other novelties. My non-vegan kids love their tsoynamis particularly the cookie dough infused Dough Boy.

gk09Y4_dAR95Oxxv66aGuQ.text: The food is too good... I can't stay away or bitter. The service is more helpful. I'm glad I'm back. Go Vegans Go...  Yum!

f4drC6KiIFFjCSlw5mzchA.text: I love this place! My family and I always come in over the weekend ...i recommend the dough boy tsoynami! the dough is to die for! The lady with the short hair is great, she knows alot and was very helpful when I couldn't make a decision on what to get.

U5HxCX9cM6-aBv1vTuHAtA.text: My friend and I went here the other night. We had an affogato, Nami cake, mint/oreo tsoynami, and 2 soy vanilla lattes.   The service is really fantastic, and the espresso is very good.

8cuXzeIaJB4PES6VDii5Og.text: Incredible. Discovered this place by word of social media, and did not regret it one bit!  I had the "Betterfinger" tsoyonami, and my boyfriend had a raspberry mocha. The tsoyonomi was delicious - after not having ice cream or anything that resembles it for a year, it was liquid gold to my palette. I also sampled his raspberry mocha, which was just as delightful. It had a rich mocha flavor with just the right amount of sweet raspberry to where it was distinct but not overpowering. The staff was also very helpful, and they seemed to have a great camaraderie behind the bar, which is always a good sign. I would go back in a heartbeat.

WdrqggBxHVX7WQtrtCBcmg.text: Best vegan ice cream. Love the chocolate clunky monkey. Usually busy. Nice outdoor seating available.

K2IbzOLB0hD9xFgmdMdQHw.text: Lots of options, which is great, but they hand mix everything, so the top of my friend's tsoynami tasted like syrup. I had the German chocolate cake tsoynami and the s'more. Both were awesome, but I think the s'more an out.

OIKyh6zSmAq1CmEhfLkAfw.text: We were always skeptical to come here because we aren't vegan and it seemed too pricey. But after hearing so many raves about this place, my husband and I rode our bikes here. The ambiance is charming and the staff is genuinely sweet.  I enjoyed a toddy while the hubby sipped on a chai tea latte. We shared an oatmeal cream, two oatmeal cookies sandwiched together by icing, addicting but a little too sweet for my taste.  Edited-  We finally tried the tsoynami and it was delicious!!!! In our minds we always rationalized by saying we would rather get blizzards at DQ. So happy we didn't this time around. My favorite is the Chai Tiramisu tsoynami and my husband loves the Fluffernuterin. We've also tried the Almond Oy Vey and the cookies 'n' cream.

f36rW-cQl9bh0yF-1RpLew.text: The Tsoynamis are amazing!! you have to try one! *&^# Dairy queen and others alike! Vegan soft serve mixed with heeps of junk is the only way to go! Their brunch is also quite impressive. They always have a Tofu scramble and hash potatoes accompany your meals, but their meals themselves are quite impressive. I Love this place!

9C-wzOfUPrZ2-ut4-HCW6g.text: I've previously had Nami's products, but yesterday was my first visit visit to their location. I love the variety of their products (baked goods, gluten-free options, etc.) and love that everything is vegan! My boyfriend and I shared the PB & Choco Tsoynami which was amazing. It's a bummer that I live so far from downtown or else I'd be here weekly. :)

_hGkYf9I-owiz7lvnydExA.text: Loved this little place! A hidden gem for vegans and vegetarians! I went very early in the morning and had a small breakfast and coffee--everything was delicious and the service was excellent. I loved the atmosphere too! They were also listening to great music. It made my experience even better. The best part was how affordable it was! I was pleasantly surprised by this place and will definitely be coming back my next time in town.

bU-65mcno5KCMQ-zWzDevA.text: Love this place!  I am not a vegan but they have the best treats in Phoenix. This is a Coffee Shop and Bakery all in one place.  I have been here a couple times and never disappointed.  They have these sinfully delicious treats called tSoynami.  They use a house-made organic soy based, tsoft tserve ice cream and you can choose your goodies.  I tried Cookie Dough tSoynami and oh my was this good!  You have ice cream, cookie dough and some chocolate sauce.  I am getting hungry just thinking about this.  Soy Captain is another favorite.  Vegan Captain Crunch and strawberries....tastes like you are having a bowl of cereal!  Nami does have a great selection of baked goodies.  They have my favorite Snickerdoodles.  I could eat these all day!

AvGTinP1yQ9dIHQo4BZBqQ.text: my favorite soynamis? the chai and the soy capitan.   although (with the exception of swizzleberry) i haven't had a soynami i didn't like. YUM!!!!

hF2cAJNpT7UTQ41FMFoyxg.text: Damn....  Just go there, go there now!!  I had the breakfast burrito, amazing!!  Got to chat with some of the staff members, everybody was super nice.

F3fje6Z3piXPa3xMVPSgJw.text: Great coffee, delicious food and a wide variety to choose from at this sunny, cheery cafe. I'd definitely bring friends back here. The vegan breakfast menu includes pastries, bagels, biscuits and gravy, some breakfast burritos, yogurt parfait, pitaya puree with granola... I had a great kale salad with a citrusy chia seed dressing for breakfast. They also make specialty espresso drinks like the kick start (mocha with cayenne). Everyone was friendly, making it a nice overall experience.

hQ9HoaB_SFEFV7rwkyPr5Q.text: i came here for the Sunday brunch in July when my boyfriend visited me. i got the benedict arnold plate and he got wing ding dang plate.  the tofu scramble that comes with every meal tastes only of tumeric. not good. they need to throw some kala namak in there to give it more of an authentic egg flavor. the hash potatoes were okay - they really needed ketchup but no ketchup was to be found.  i tried one of my boyfriend's wings and it was one of the foulest things i have ever tasted. there was way too much vinegar in the sauce. yet, he still somehow loved them. i'm convinced that boy has no taste whatsoever.  i've never had nonvegan hollandaise sauce so i have nothing to compare it to, but the hollandaise sauce that came on my plate just tasted like mustard to me. which, i imagine, is not the way hollandaise is supposed to taste.  despite all this, the donuts are TO DIE FOR. I got a maple bar and ohhhhhh my god! it tasted just like the real deal!   i don't know WHAT they make their canadian bacon out of, but it is the best dang canadian bacon i have EVER had! it tastes JUST like regular ham!   on your way out, they also have some refreshing complimentary cucumber water which i really enjoyed.   i wish i could give this place more stars simply for being an all-vegan restaurant, but the food is either hit or miss. would i come here again? absolutely. but probably just for the amazing donuts and canadian bacon. :^)

lwXWY5mRP0GF6BhyavXNPw.text: By far some of the best food in Phoenix, AZ is served here.  Their food is well prepared, fresh and always delicious!! Excellent place to fill up on even if your in a bit of a hurry.  Stop here and try it, you will not regret you did.

eLyQDwjEwJAGJmUmJSOUXA.text: Quick takeout service and the Oatmeal cream cookie was so much better than I expected. Made me realize I can eat plant based without giving up flavor.

gZqkEu0s7CRRI5oQT4WDpA.text: Oh my goodness! I went here for the first time tonight and got a Mystery Mash Tsoynami.. I love the service, and my treat was deeeeeelicious!! I'll definitely be coming back

Sometimes you get you order in less then 10 minutes, and other times it takes upwards of 20-30 minutes. The one thing that is consistent is the unfriendliness of the staff. If I was rating the food alone I would give 4 stars but because of the customer service, I give them 3 stars.

E0qa_yNs-oyu4-NEx1Y38A.text: Never a negative experience! My favorites: the soynami, hazelnut lattes, the donuts, scones, cookies, & the nami mcbagel.  Awesome atmosphere, great location, lovely artwork, & super close to Green to catch dinner before.

ionBZgjyoiFYW1Anb9xqpg.text: I'm a three or four per week Tsoynami addict. PB&C, cookies and cream and dougboy are personal favorites. Also try a slice of Vegan cake. Only non-dairy dessert I've found that's as good as a Tsoynami is in Tel Aviv!!

CvbvTMG-7DTjS6Q7rf8dUg.text: Delicious Cappucino & perfect Peanut Butter Cookie

yVr3byQJ07r1OshlSFc2Vw.text: I went for the brunch today.  First of all I just don't understand why they didn't serve brunch at Green, that's where the kitchen is. They were very adamant about waiting until 9am until anyone could place a brunch order even though the place was filling up before 9am.  Though once orders were placed food came quickly.  The plates were brought over from Green and probably played a hand in why the food wasn't hot, but it was more likely due to it being pre made, quite possibly the day ahead of time, and not heated well, which in turn made for a very dry tofu scramble.  I got the Sage Sausage Hashsheesh, unfortunately no sage flavor just one note flavor, even so, it would have tasted better Hot and it would have been nice to have toast with it as well.  By the time we left it was standing room only.   I may be pointing out the obvious here but Nami should stick to being a coffee and pastry shop and let real meals be at Green where food can be served hot from the kitchen into a dining room that can accommodate more people. Maybe consider having an option to order brunch at Nami for the overflow but to have it solely there is asinine.  P.S. I'd like to add that the first time I visited Nami I ordered the Fluffernutterin Soynami which is ORGANIC peanut butter, banana, ricemellow fluff and toasted marshmellow flavor and I stood there and watched her scoop in SKIPPY Peanut Butter=Not Cool=False Advertising=Fail!

V7L023LNO2BTv2Sg-KpijA.text: I cannot rave enough about this place - the environment, the people, but specifically, those tsoynami's. As a dairy free lady living in this city, Nami is everything I could ask for when it comes to desserts! I'm a local at Nami, and you know it's bad when they know your name at the order stand. emaVawRA_CG4TIHm-17o-w.text: Only place in town to get anything like it - Tsoynamis - like vegan blizzards. They have a ton of other vegan treats and make cakes for special events too. We recently discovered weekend brunch - all vegan breakfasts, coffee drinks, and they even have Bloody Marys.

L8Iw4KIVOyQbtxXrGXJtlQ.text: Popped in here while I waited for my food at Green to be served. Ordered a latte and waited to be called. LCxKA1gixrW5X9lmjdRO-Q.text: A friend discovered Nami shortly after I assisted him in his transition to the plant based lifestyle. We originally referred to tsynami's as "sex in a cup", they are that good. Now that chocolate is offered, they are even better, if that is even possible. They always have gluten free options available and Sunday brunch is so filling and delicious. I am thrilled that breakfast is offered daily now as well. Coffee and dairy free milk selection is fantastic and staff is always friendly and inviting, often remembering me, even after long absences. I recommend this to anyone who is willing to explore plant based options. It is a great place for those transitioning or have an issue with dairy.

TGKfwyE-flvkP4lHJStaug.text: WOW.. to be honest WOW  I thought I had some good vegetarian food before, but this place owns it all.   Best Mock meat i have ever had! My fiancee got the mock chicken, (some noodle dish, i forget the name, but it was around the top of the menu), I got a tofu version of the spicy noodle bowl (whatever their name was i forget, i will know it if i see it)  Needless to say i really enjoyed each dish. I would love to try other things on their menu and I think...no i KNOW we will be back some time too.  Their coffee shop is freakn awesome, which is next door. I got a drink there, my fiancee got some vegan pastries after me telling her don't cause i never had a good one before.  Well i was wrong they were pretty good cookies...(though i don't like to mention it too often). the coffee was great too. It helps when you have friendly fun baristas working. I've had the sausage hash as a wet chimichanga and it was delicious (though I don't know how anything deep fried cannot be delicious). Last sunday, I got the benedict arnold and it too was great. P8mSI9Zk_ZrLcT2V9_G4vg.text: Of course I got a tSoynami when I came here after reading about them! Soy-based vegan soft serve with goodies mixed in? Win! I went with one of the gluten-free ones (as noted on the menu), the PB 'n' Chocolate one ... because ... peanut butter. 'Nuff said.  Peanut butter and chocolate is always an amazing combination, of course. They went well with the soy soft serve, although my only issue is that the soy soft serve is not really that soft. I don't know if it was just the batch that I got or if that's how it is because it's soy milk-based and therefore lower in fat than traditional dairy soft serve ice cream, but this was rather icy and gritty. The texture more resembled a sorbet than soft serve.  But still delicious nonetheless!  Service also didn't leave a fantastic impression on me. The ladies behind the counter was a tad busy with previous orders but it wasn't until at least four or five minutes before one of them acknowledged that I was standing there waiting and said that they would be right with me. I don't mind waiting, but I just wish from a customer service standpoint that they would have acknowledged that I was standing there waiting patiently for quite some time.

wUXN32RxQcbnewxB2WPkyw.text: Had an amazing tofu scrable here will definitely come back to this cute cosy little place!

ueZ_yh6QOHrG0IV7yeiCOg.text: The bad thing about Nami is that everything is so amazingly delicious, deciding what to get is very difficult.  Nami is a 100% vegan baked goods/ sweets/ breakfast/brunch spot, which is owned by the same person who owns the Green New American Vegetarian restaurants. It's located next door to Green's PHX location.   BRUNCH: Served Sundays, 9a-2p. Arrive early or prepare to wait in a long, winding-out-the-door line. Try to be savvy by calling ahead (as I have), but you'll still have to wait in that line to pay for your order.   My favorite brunch items from the regular menu are...  -Biscuits & Gravy. Fresh biscuits smothered in chorizo gravy, topped w/ chopped green onions. It is so good! It comes with papas and tofu scramble (try the scramble with salsa or Sriracha sauce!), plus fresh and sweet pineapple wedges to cleanse the palate.   -Wing Ding Dang. Their famous spicy/buffalo "wings" (they really aren't that spicy, IMO) served with papas & scramble. I like it naked (aka as a plate instead of a burrito).  My carnivorous family loves this dish too.  If you wanna be fancy (*singing* I'm so fancy!), mix it up, or add it up, rather. Because I like the Biscuits & Gravy + the wings, I usually add a side order of wings to my B&G meal for only $5 more.   SPECIALS: They feature a different brunch special every Sunday, which is ingenious really; it keeps things fresh, and keeps the customers coming back. I'll be thinking, "Oh, I'm going to stay at home this weekend." Then, BAM! They'll post pancakes or the Flying Saucer as the special and all my plans have to be rearranged. The great thing about the specials (aside from them being, well...special) is that if you fall in love with one (and you shall!), it will likely be featured again sometime in the future.  My fav specials, thus far...  -anything with pancakes. Be it the Grand Slam, blueberry pancakes, etc., they are ALL delicious. I do wish they'd add pancakes to the full time menu.  - (I'm going to butcher the name) The Flying Saucer Full of Secrets? It's a Mexicana breakfast pizza w/ chorizo, black beans, hominy corn, guacamole, lettuce, enchilada sauce, papas, & scramble (I omit it, but cheese & sour cream too), atop a crispy fried tortilla. IT. IS. SO. DARN. AMAZING! It's huge too! Share it or save 1/2 for later (it warms up pretty good if you take off the guacamole first; no one wants hot guac)  -DaeDae's "Chicken" & Waffles. A vegan take on a southern classic, and they nail it!  -Bad @$$ Texas Summer Tacos (that's really the name!).  Tacos stuffed with fried avocados & refried pinto beans. Yum!  The only thing I'm not a fan of is the grits. Maybe I'm just a little too southern for these new fangled grits.  People who like them seem to love them. See for yourself.  BREAKFAST: It wasn't alway so, but they serve breakfast, Mon-Sat, from 7a-11a, so the Biscuits & Gravy, and the Wing Ding Dang are now available daily!   My favorite among the new breakfast items is the Country Breakfast Burrito. It's a big ole thang too!  Organic scramble, tempeh "bacon", papas, peppers, onions, & syrup (sans vegan cheese for moi) stuffed into la tortilla. Such a great and super filling breakfast!   OTHER: Aside from meals, there is also a plethora of baked goods from which you may choose, including various tantalizing donut flavors (these donuts are as big as your face!), cakes, cupcakes, cookies, pies, etc. I only drink water, but there is a humongous list of coffee/cappuccino, tea, juice, and vegan milk options. They have a (very) few vegan grocery items too.   Look out for the Nookie (ask about it!) & Sunday sundae specials! Live music sometimes.   TSOYNAMI: NOW let's talk about the Tsoynami! Vegan soft serve, originally in vanilla, but as of 07Aug14, they introduced the CHOCOLATE TSOYNAMI! AND you can SWIRL (chocolate & vanilla)!  My FAV Tsoynami creations -   From the regular menu  -Soy Capitan - vegan Captain Crunch & strawberries mixed in. Berry cool!  -Dough Boy - chocolate chip cookie dough & chocolate syrup mixed in. YUM!  -Cookies n' Cream - Newman's chocolate cookies + chocolate syrup. Classic!  From the "specials" rotation -Chocolate Monsoon - chocolate cake + chocolate syrup mixed in. HELLO!  -Orange Creamsicle - orange magic + icing (you heard me!) + whip cream = heavenly dreams that taste like childhood summers.   -Raspberry Beret - raspberry & cream cheese pastry puff & raspberry puree mixed in. AMAZING! (I may or may not have been singing Prince's song whilst indulging.)  MY CREATION - pretzels, toffee nut, chocolate syrup mixed into the soft serve. Create your own too!  If you don't want all that extra, you may eat the Tsoynami plain (think spiral soft serve) in a cup or cone. They can drizzle some of their naturally flavored syrups on it too, if you'd like. I recommend the caramel, toffee nut, and chocolate syrups.   A cup of Tsoynami is a LOT of ice cream. If you'd like to share it, tell the cashier and they'll split it up for you.  Nami for all!

One thing I will say is parking is ATROCIOUS and lines can be just as bad. With some patience, it's definitely worth coming here. RWZxYLLFsTvXMzvp8mmaTg.text: Employee with short brown bob cut styled hair who was working on 05/30/2018 on the close shift Is the reason for this bad review. I came in at 9:25 and asked if I could order one thing, they closed at 9:30. I understand that I came close to closing time but I drove 100mph on the I10 to get nami for my ill relative. And I called ahead and was told that they would take my order as long as it was before close. I'm extremely annoyed and disappointed with nami and their shitty employee especially since I drove 30 minutes from Scottsdale Road and the 101. HORRIBLE CUSTOMER SERVICE. The vegans should be ashamed!!! This is why I eat icecream that's has products in it that we're involved in extreme animal abuse because those icecream shops have never let me down.
